title: Has anyone tried daily low-dose tadalafil like Vidalista 2.5mg?
content:
Iâ€™ve been reading about different treatment options for erectile dysfunction and noticed that some doctors recommend low-dose daily tadalafil instead of on-demand tablets.

One option I came across is Vidalista 2.5mg, which contains tadalafil in a lower strength meant for daily use. From what I understand, this approach helps maintain steady levels of the medication in the body, allowing more flexibility and spontaneity rather than timing a pill before activity.

Itâ€™s also interesting that tadalafil is sometimes prescribed for benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH), so it may help men who experience both urinary symptoms and mild ED. Of course, this kind of medication should only be used under medical guidance, especially for people with heart conditions or those taking other prescriptions.

Iâ€™m curious if anyone here has experience with daily tadalafilâ€”how it compares to higher-dose, on-demand options, and whether it feels more consistent over time.

For reference, this is the product page I was reading: https://edpillsforever.com/product/vidalista-2-5-mg/

title: "Email link..."
content:
I am unable to find an answer (hours on the Internet) to this specific problem that has appeared out of nowhere:

Under File in the Menu Bar the "Email Link..." does not work anymore. If I want to send a thing I'm looking at to my Thunderbird email (and which I use Hover), most often is a You Tube video. But I do this for other things I start reading, but I don't have time for. This has worked for a very long time. It was always so easy. Now when I click on Email Link all I get is a blue circle-I think it rotates sometimes. It disappears in a second or less. I get nothing.

I do have Windows 11 and up-to-date Firefox. I am fairly sure it continued to work after I got a new computer Nov. 4th with W11 on it. I believe I lost this function within the last 6-8 weeks.
